cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper involves human psychophysics experiments on eye movement behavior while searching for a target object. The paper also proposes a model that uses a pre-trained 2D convolutional architecture to extract features and compute a 2D similarity map. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves human-computer interaction and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
